Cohen Likes Mobility Apps, Sees Market ’Grinding’, NY Times Says

-- B y   R e b e c c a   E v a n s
-- 
2011-02-16T04:57:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/cohen-likes-mobility-apps-sees-market-grinding-ny-times-says.html
  Steven A. Cohen , founder of SAC
Capital Advisers, described the current stock market as
“grinding every day,” in an interview with the New York Times.  He told the newspaper “underneath stocks are exploding, and
everything I’m seeing today looks bullish.”   Cohen said his favourite sectors were mobility applications
and businesses that create faster networks.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
